==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gaucho
<hw>Gau"cho</hw> <pr>(gou"ch⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>,
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Gauchos</plw> <pr>(gou"ch⟦osl⟧z)</pr></plu>
<ety>[Sp.]</ety> <def>One of the native inhabitants of the South
American pampas, of Spanish-American descent. They live mostly by
rearing cattle. Hence, a South American cowboy, especially on the
pampas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A member of an Indian population, somewhat affected
by Spanish blood, in the archipelagoes off the Chilean coast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gaud</ent>⟦br⟧
